Interface KbTerm

  • All Superinterfaces:
    KbObject, KbObject.KbObjectWithArity
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BinaryPredicate, Context, FirstOrderCollection, KbCollection, KbFunction, KbIndividual, KbPredicate, Relation, SecondOrderCollection
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryPredicateWrapper, ContextWrapper, FirstOrderCollectionWrapper, KbCollectionWrapper, KbFunctionWrapper, KbIndividualWrapper, KbPredicateWrapper, KbTermWrapper, RelationWrapper, SecondOrderCollectionWrapper

    public interface KbTerm
extends KbObject.KbObjectWithArity
    The top-level interface for most kinds of KbObjects that are not Sentences.

      • provablyNotInstanceOf

        boolean provablyNotInstanceOf(KbCollection col,
                              Context ctx)
        Determine whether this is provably not an instance of col. This means that there is no way to convert this into an instance of col without editing or removing current KB assertions.
        Parameters:
        col - the collection which this is to be tested against
        ctx - the context in which the semantic test should be performed
        Returns:
        whether this is provably not an instance of col

      • replaceTerms

        <O> O replaceTerms(Map substitutions)
            throws KbTypeException,
                   CreateException
        Non-destructively replace a set of objects within a non-atomic term. This does not modify the original term, but instead returns a new one. Any KBObject or Java

        Note: a common use of this method is to replace indexical terms, so you may want to see KbObject.isIndexical() for more details about them. However, this method can be used to replace any element within a term, not just indexicals.

        Type Parameters:
        O - the referent's expected type
        Parameters:
        substitutions - the replacement mapping
        Returns:
        a new term with the replaced terms
        Throws:
        KbTypeException
        CreateException

      • rename

        KbTerm rename(String nameString)
       throws InvalidNameException
        Change the name of an atomic term to nameString. This method only applies to atomic terms (i.e., CycL constants); attempts to rename non-atomic terms will result in an exception, as will attempts to rename constants that are mentioned in server code.
        Parameters:
        nameString - the new name
        Returns:
        the renamed KbTerm
        Throws:
        InvalidNameException - in cases where the rename cannot be completed; e.g. the name does not conform to Cyc constant-naming conventions
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the object being renamed is not KbObject.isAtomic()
        See Also:
        KbObject.isAtomic()

      • addComment

        Fact addComment(String comment,
                Context ctx)
         throws KbTypeException,
                CreateException
        Add a new comment for this in the context specified

        In the CycKB comments can be added only on #$CycLIndexedTerms, which include CycLReifiableDenotationalTerm and CycLAssertion. An exception will be thrown if attempted to add a comment on Quoted terms, Sentence, Variable and Symbol. This means that only subclasses of KbTerm and Assertion can have comments.

        Parameters:
        ctx - the context where the comment is created. Cannot be null.
        comment - the comment string
        Returns:
        the fact created
        Throws:
        CreateException
        KbTypeException

      • instantiatesSentence

        Sentence instantiatesSentence(KbCollection collection)
                       throws KbTypeException,
                              CreateException
        This method returns the Sentence (#$isa this collection). The key difference between this and instantiates(com.cyc.kb.KbCollection) is that, this method does not make any assertion in the KB. The sentence form of the assertion is generally useful when seeking user feedback before asserting into the KB. Use Sentence.assertIn(com.cyc.kb.Context) to assert the sentence in a Context.
        Parameters:
        collection - the collection of which this KbIndividual is an instance
        Returns:
        the #$isa sentence between this and col
        Throws:
        KbTypeException
        CreateException
